data.title: Legislator Details
data.text:
Vital Records Information:

Marital Information:

married Brad Delaney; children: 2, Blake and 1 other

Number of Children: 2

Background

Education:

attended Leslie and Holt public schools and Lansing Community College; BS, Michigan State University in Agribusiness Management, 1999; JD, Michigan State University College of Law, 2004

Biographical Sketch:

She owned and operated Byrum Hardware in Charlotte. She was a past president of the Charlotte Chamber of Commerce. Barb was Chair of the Ingham County Economic Development Board and served as Secretary of the Ingham County Brownfield Redevelopment Authority. Barb served as board member of the Retired Senior Volunteer Program (RSVP). She was elected Ingham County Clerk at the November 2012 General Election.

Notable Facts:

Daughter of State Rep./Sen Diane Byrum and Jim Byrum.
